      "content": "Wait, are you sure? I was looking at a different draft earlier and it said something about \"mutual agreement required.\" If I tell the board we have this massive 5% loophole, they're going to kill the whole deal and delay our fuel supply for months. That would be way worse for the budget than a small price bump.\n\nIs there any way to interpret that \"market volatility\" part as requiring us to approve the spike first? Like, can't we argue that \"implementing\" a change implies we have to be notified and agree so we can update our systems? I really need this to be a stable, predictable contract. If we can just say it's not a unilateral right, we can sign today.",
